HLS 26RS-6197 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 391
BY REPRESENTATIVE MARTINEZ
COURTS: Creates a task force to study the effectiveness of the 18th Judicial District Court
Drug Court Program
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create and provide for a task force to study the effectiveness, operations, counseling and
3 treatment services, funding, mental health evaluations, and outcomes associated with
4 the 18th Judicial District Court Drug Court Program and behavioral health services
5 provided to incarcerated individuals within the 18th Judicial District.
6 WHEREAS, substance abuse, addiction, and untreated mental illness continue to
7 impact families, public safety, workforce participation, and the criminal justice system
8 throughout this state; and
9 WHEREAS, specialty courts, including drug courts, have been recognized as
10 alternatives to incarceration that may reduce recidivism and improve long-term recovery
11 outcomes; and
12 WHEREAS, counseling services, behavioral health treatment, accountability
13 measures, and recovery support are critical components of successful specialty court
14 programs; and
15 WHEREAS, incarcerated individuals suffering from mental illness often require
16 timely evaluations, treatment coordination, counseling, medication management, and
17 continuity of care; and
18 WHEREAS, the 18th Judicial District Court Drug Court Program serves participants
19 from Iberville, Pointe Coupee, and West Baton Rouge Parishes and plays an important role
20 in rehabilitation and accountability efforts; and
