1 WHEREAS, the legislature has an interest in understanding the effectiveness,
2 financial impact, counseling practices, mental health services, and long-term outcomes
3 associated with specialty court programs and correctional behavioral health services
4 operating within this state; and
5 WHEREAS, a comprehensive review of the 18th Judicial District Court Drug Court
6 Program and behavioral health services may assist policymakers in identifying barriers to
7 treatment access, funding needs, counseling effectiveness, and opportunities for program
8 improvement or expansion.
9 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
10 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby create the 18th Judicial District Drug Court and
11 Behavioral Health Services Task Force to study the operations, effectiveness, counseling
12 services, treatment implementation, mental health evaluations, and continuity of care
13 associated with the 18th Judicial District Court Drug Court Program and behavioral health
14 services provided to incarcerated individuals within the 18th Judicial District.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
16 members:
17 (1) One representative from the 18th Judicial District Court or his designee.
18 (2) One representative from the Louisiana Supreme Court Drug and Specialty Court
19 Office or his designee.
20 (3) One representative from the Louisiana Department of Health or his designee.
21 (4) One representative from the Department of Public Safety and Corrections or his
22 designee.
23 (5) One licensed mental health professional or behavioral health provider serving
24 the district or his designee.
25 (6) One licensed substance abuse counselor serving the district or his designee.
26 (7) One representative from a local correctional facility within the district or his
27 designee.
28 (8) One representative from workforce development or reentry services or his
29 designee.
