1 (9) One member appointed by the speaker of the House of Representatives or his
2 designee.
3 (10) One member appointed by the president of the Senate or his designee.
4 (11) The state representative who represents House District No. 60.
5 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the representative from the Louisiana Supreme
6 Court Drug and Specialty Court Office shall serve as the chairman of the task force.
7 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall examine and provide
8 findings regarding the following:
9 (1) Recidivism rates and participant outcomes.
10 (2) Graduation and completion rates of the drug court program.
11 (3) Counseling and behavioral health treatment services utilized by the program.
12 (4) The implementation, oversight, and effectiveness of counseling services and
13 recovery programming.
14 (5) The availability and timeliness of mental health evaluations for incarcerated
15 individuals requiring behavioral health services.
16 (6) Coordination between correctional facilities, behavioral health providers, and
17 treatment programs.
18 (7) Medication continuity and follow-up treatment services after release or program
19 completion.
20 (8) Treatment availability and barriers to access.
21 (9) Employment and workforce reintegration outcomes.
22 (10) Cost comparisons between incarceration and specialty court participation.
23 (11) Funding sources and sustainability of the program and related behavioral health
24 services.
25 (12) Recommendations for improving counseling, treatment, mental health services,
26 and recovery outcomes while reducing repeat offenses.
27 (13) Opportunities for program expansion or additional legislative support.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene for its first meeting
29 no later than sixty days after the effective date of this Resolution, at the call of the chairman.
